Password Generator
This code generates a random password of a specified length. The password can include letters, numbers, and special characters.

How to use
To generate a password, run the following command:
java
java -jar password-generator.jar

The code will prompt you for the length of the password. Enter the desired length and press Enter.

The code will generate a random password and print it to the console.

You can generate another password by pressing Enter. To exit the code, press Ctrl+C.

Options
The code has the following options:

-l or --length: The length of the password. The default length is 12.
-s or --special: Whether to include special characters in the password. The default is to include special characters.
Example
The following example generates a password of 16 characters that includes special characters:

java -jar password-generator.jar -l 16 -s
